

Find a connecting path between word A and word B,
using a number of intermediate words.


chair
hair
pair
par
pad
pod
plod


The usual rules for connections between words are:

1) word 1 is connected to word 2 if they are the same length
   and differ by only one letter.
2) If word 2 can be formed by deleting one letter from
   word 1, they are connected.

